    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-03-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="31"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Furniss</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 33.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to report that I to-day ascertained from
                    the French chargé d’affaires that he had come to an agreement with the Haitian
                    Government, whereby the French-Haitian treaty, which had been <pb facs="1060"
                        n="902" xml:id="pg_902"/> denounced by Haiti and was to expire April 30, is
                    to be extended for six months, to give oportunity for further negotiation
                    looking to a permanent treaty.</p>
                <p>The agreement has been written, and only awaits authorization from the French
                    Government for the formal signing.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. W. Furniss.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
